\title{File Organizer}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Intelligently organizes your files and folders across your computer by}

\subtree{
\title{File Organizer}
\p{This skill acts as your personal organization assistant, helping you maintain a clean, logical file structure across your computer without the mental overhead of constant manual organization.}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use This Skill}
\ul{
\li{Your Downloads folder is a chaotic mess}
\li{You can't find files because they're scattered everywhere}
\li{You have duplicate files taking up space}
\li{Your folder structure doesn't make sense anymore}
\li{You want to establish better organization habits}
\li{You're starting a new project and need a good structure}
\li{You're cleaning up before archiving old projects}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{What This Skill Does}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Analyzes Current Structure}: Reviews your folders and files to understand what you have}
\li{\strong{Finds Duplicates}: Identifies duplicate files across your system}
\li{\strong{Suggests Organization}: Proposes logical folder structures based on your content}
\li{\strong{Automates Cleanup}: Moves, renames, and organizes files with your approval}
\li{\strong{Maintains Context}: Makes smart decisions based on file types, dates, and content}
\li{\strong{Reduces Clutter}: Identifies old files you probably don't need anymore}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{How to Use}
\subtree{
\title{From Your Home Directory}
\pre{\startverb
cd ~
\stopverb}

\p{Then run Claude Code and ask for help:}

\pre{\startverb
Help me organize my Downloads folder
\stopverb}

\pre{\startverb
Find duplicate files in my Documents folder
\stopverb}

\pre{\startverb
Review my project directories and suggest improvements
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Specific Organization Tasks}
\pre{\startverb
Organize these downloads into proper folders based on what they are
\stopverb}

\pre{\startverb
Find duplicate files and help me decide which to keep
\stopverb}

\pre{\startverb
Clean up old files I haven't touched in 6+ months
\stopverb}

\pre{\startverb
Create a better folder structure for my [work/projects/photos/etc]
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Instructions}
\p{When a user requests file organization help:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Understand the Scope}}
\li{Which directory needs organization? (Downloads, Documents, entire home folder?)}
\li{What's the main problem? (Can't find things, duplicates, too messy, no structure?)}
\li{Any files or folders to avoid? (Current projects, sensitive data?)}
\li{How aggressively to organize? (Conservative vs. comprehensive cleanup)}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Analyze Current State}}
\li{Total files and folders}
\li{File type breakdown}
\li{Size distribution}
\li{Date ranges}
\li{Obvious organization issues}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Identify Organization Patterns}}
\li{Documents (PDFs, DOCX, TXT)}
\li{Images (JPG, PNG, SVG)}
\li{Videos (MP4, MOV)}
\li{Archives (ZIP, TAR, DMG)}
\li{Code/Projects (directories with code)}
\li{Spreadsheets (XLSX, CSV)}
\li{Presentations (PPTX, KEY)}
\li{Work vs. Personal}
\li{Active vs. Archive}
\li{Project-specific}
\li{Reference materials}
\li{Temporary/scratch files}
\li{Current year/month}
\li{Previous years}
\li{Very old (archive candidates)}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Find Duplicates}}
\li{Show all file paths}
\li{Display sizes and modification dates}
\li{Recommend which to keep (usually newest or best-named)}
\li{\strong{Important}: Always ask for confirmation before deleting}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Propose Organization Plan}}
\li{X files across Y folders}
\li{[Size] total}
\li{File types: [breakdown]}
\li{Issues: [list problems]}
\li{\strong{Create new folders}: [list]}
\li{\strong{Move files}:}
\li{X PDFs → Work/Documents/}
\li{Y images → Personal/Photos/}
\li{Z old files → Archive/}
\li{\strong{Rename files}: [any renaming patterns]}
\li{\strong{Delete}: [duplicates or trash files]}
\li{[List any files you're unsure about]}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Execute Organization}}
\li{Always confirm before deleting anything}
\li{Log all moves for potential undo}
\li{Preserve original modification dates}
\li{Handle filename conflicts gracefully}
\li{Stop and ask if you encounter unexpected situations}
}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Provide Summary and Maintenance Tips}}
\li{Created [X] new folders}
\li{Organized [Y] files}
\li{Freed [Z] GB by removing duplicates}
\li{Archived [W] old files}
\li{\strong{Weekly}: Sort new downloads}
\li{\strong{Monthly}: Review and archive completed projects}
\li{\strong{Quarterly}: Check for new duplicates}
\li{\strong{Yearly}: Archive old files}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Find files modified this week}
\p{find . -type f -mtime -7}
}

