\subtree{
\title{Examples}
\subtree{
\title{Example 1: Organizing Downloads (From Justin Dielmann)}
\p{\strong{User}: "My Downloads folder is a mess with 500+ files. Help me organize it."}

\p{\strong{Process}:}

\ol{
\li{Analyzes Downloads folder}
\li{Finds patterns: work docs, personal photos, installers, random PDFs}
\li{Proposes structure:}
\li{Downloads/}
\li{Work/}
\li{Personal/}
\li{Installers/ (DMG, PKG files)}
\li{Archive/}
\li{ToSort/ (things needing decisions)}
\li{Asks for confirmation}
\li{Moves files intelligently based on content and names}
\li{Results: 500 files → 5 organized folders}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Example 2: Finding and Removing Duplicates}
\p{\strong{User}: "Find duplicate files in my Documents and help me decide which to keep."}

\p{\strong{Output}:}

\pre{\startverb
# Found 23 Sets of Duplicates (156 MB total)

## Duplicate Set 1: "proposal.pdf"
- `/Documents/proposal.pdf` (2.3 MB, modified: 2024-03-15)
- `/Documents/old/proposal.pdf` (2.3 MB, modified: 2024-03-15)
- `/Desktop/proposal.pdf` (2.3 MB, modified: 2024-03-10)

**Recommendation**: Keep `/Documents/proposal.pdf` (most recent in correct location)
Delete the other 2 copies?

[Continue for all duplicates...]
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Example 3: Restructuring Projects Folder}
\p{\strong{User}: "Review my ~/Projects directory and suggest improvements."}

\p{\strong{Output}:}

\pre{\startverb
# Analysis of ~/Projects

## Current Structure Issues
- Mix of active and archived projects (3+ years old)
- No consistent naming convention
- Some projects at root, others in random subfolders
- Duplicate folders (project-name, project-name-old, project-name-v2)

## Proposed Structure

\stopverb}

\p{Projects/ ├── Active/ │   ├── client-work/ │   ├── side-projects/ │   └── learning/ ├── Archive/ │   ├── 2022/ │   ├── 2023/ │   └── 2024/ └── Templates/}

\pre{\startverb

## Specific Changes
1. Move 12 projects not touched since 2022 → Archive/
2. Consolidate 4 duplicate project folders
3. Rename projects to consistent format: "client-name-project-name"
4. Create Archive for old work

Want me to implement this?
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Example 4: Organizing Photos by Date}
\p{\strong{User}: "Organize my photo folders by year and month."}

\p{\strong{Output}: Creates structure like:}

\pre{\startverb
Photos/
├── 2023/
│   ├── 01-January/
│   ├── 02-February/
│   └── ...
├── 2024/
│   ├── 01-January/
│   └── ...
└── Unsorted/
\stopverb}

\p{Then moves photos based on EXIF data or file modification dates.}
}
}

